com.linkedin.parseq.trace
Interface Trace

public interface Trace

A Trace represents a point-in-time snapshot of a Task's state. Generally, this point in time will be after the task has completed, but traces can also be taken of tasks that are currently executing.

Traces are immutable and thread-safe. Use TraceBuilder to create new traces.

Use a TraceCodec to serialize and deserialize Traces.

Author:
Chi Chan (ckchan@linkedin.com), Chris Pettitt
